Bi2O3 powder was synthesized using a method described in a recent research report [28]. To synthesize the Bi2O3/Cdots composite, 500 mg of bismuth nitrate was mixed with Cdots (5–15 wt%) in 50 ml of 5% nitric acid at 500 rpm for 5 min. The solution was then added to a modified microwave reactor at 75 °C, with the stirring time varying from 10 to 30 min and the power ranging between 300 and 800 W (factors and detailed research levels are presented in Table 1
                        ). The experimental design was analyzed using design expert software (Stat-Ease Design-Expert 13). To obtain the final product, 250 ml of sodium hydroxide was added to the solution and stirred for 2 h until precipitates formed, which were then annealed in a furnace at 450 °C for 4 h. The detailed synthesis procedure is shown in Fig. 1
                        (a). The Cdots concentration, power, and synthesis duration of the solution inserted into the microwave reactor were varied to synthesize the Bi2O3/Cdots composites.
